<subSubSection id="9F3EC72086543158E27422FF7AB90CB5" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C548294378FA9CF4E650172103F4EBD4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2AE82285E580C0F0FA1BD3C1EF9B0367" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName id="651AE06868D0D32B6B0D5ACAC7CC9078" authorityName="gen. nov. et" authorityYear="2022" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Balkanodesminus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Balkanodesminus dentatoides" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dentatoides">
<emphasis id="70EF622958AB6704D01B8977631D2887" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Balkanodesminus dentatoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. et sp. nov. and 
<taxonomicName id="F02F9CE9D5E00C87649F4C6136092A29" genus="B." lsidName="B. dentatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis id="2E370E32F3E434EE24C838C293A09CB7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov., comb. nov., stat. nov. by the presence of longer (vs. shorter) metatergal setae and their smaller (vs. greater) number of rows, as well as by the presence of more simplified gonopods, with uniramous (vs. biramous) distal solenomeral process, and smaller and smooth (vs. larger and denticulated) lamella of solenophore. From 
<taxonomicName id="C13299FD7E998B06DE7BDBAE5181D01B" genus="B." lsidName="B. serbicus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="serbicus">
<emphasis id="7A280376C375E3C5CB35985242166088" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. serbicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. et sp. nov., with which it shares similar habitus and similar gonopods, it differs by the presence of larger (vs. smaller) lamella of solenophore, slender, almost straight (vs. more robust and sigmoid) distal projection of solenophore, distal projection without (vs. with) basal lobe and slenderer (vs. stouter) solenomere and distal solenomeral process, where the solenomere exceeds the distal solenomeral process by 
<normalizedToken id="CCA3FC189BDC996808FDB9DCC41DF2E8" originalValue="½">1/2</normalizedToken>
(vs. 
<normalizedToken id="166CD38CAA28F1DDC604B1FF62D7A350" originalValue="¼">1/4</normalizedToken>
) of its length.
</paragraph>
<caption id="26E5E6D87D96D9DFDBC8780DBF1CC832" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1097.83916.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/674284" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
