<subSubSection id="6C567CCF0A01A3CB849D3EB9F2DBAB1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4AAF86977C9B8A4AD6522187EEEAF6BB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2551BC2A9C3BB14FA3ABC274715BD99F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species shows a somewhat scattered distribution (see Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6DD43BB708FA3564AE01A56BE02DFE34" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Distribution of cavernicolous Trichopolydesmidae from the Carpathian-Balkan arch and the Rhodope Mountains." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1097.83916.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/674296" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">18</figureCitation>
). It is present in caves starting from Vidin Municipality, through Chuprene and Chiprovtsi municipalities all the way to Vratsa municipality. These are Varkan Cave, Vidin Municipality (
<bibRefCitation id="F5776E9305E55F40FC58613611BA7A43" author="Strasser, K" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="411 - 470" refId="B56" refString="Strasser, K, 1973. Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens, III. Annales Zoologici 30 (15): 411 - 470" title="Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens, III." volume="30" year="1973">Strasser 1973</bibRefCitation>
), Desni suhi pech Cave, Chuprene Municipality (
<bibRefCitation id="4AAE3B267DF3C4118DFBB3BF0851289A" author="Strasser, K" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="411 - 470" refId="B56" refString="Strasser, K, 1973. Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens, III. Annales Zoologici 30 (15): 411 - 470" title="Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens, III." volume="30" year="1973">Strasser 1973</bibRefCitation>
), Mishin kamik Cave (type locality) and Vreloto v seloto Cave, both Chiprovtsi Municipality (
<bibRefCitation id="B432B51D4C506A04D15D2DB0E35DF8FB" author="Strasser, K" journalOrPublisher="Senckenbergiana Biologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="437 - 470" refId="B53" refString="Strasser, K, 1962. Diplopoden aus Bulgarien und Jugoslawien. Senckenbergiana Biologica 43 (6): 437 - 470" title="Diplopoden aus Bulgarien und Jugoslawien." volume="43" year="1962">Strasser 1962</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="AD665E2873405B9D049438C6DC0B86EE" author="Strasser, K" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="325 - 385" refId="B54" refString="Strasser, K, 1966a. Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens. Annales Zoologici 23 (12): 325 - 385" title="Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens." volume="23" year="1966 a">1966a</bibRefCitation>
), as well as Mladenovata peshtera Cave and Ponora Cave, Vratsa Municipality (
<bibRefCitation id="C4F85DAB4C2C229C3615946C368BFA57" author="Strasser, K" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="325 - 385" refId="B54" refString="Strasser, K, 1966a. Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens. Annales Zoologici 23 (12): 325 - 385" title="Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens." volume="23" year="1966 a">Strasser 1966a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2407B21AC293396F157F84714C5FEEF3" author="Stoev, P" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Bulgarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="145 - 154" refId="B50" refString="Stoev, P, 2004. New distributional records of millipedes from Bulgarian caves (Myriapoda: Diplopoda). Acta Zoologica Bulgarica 56 (2): 145 - 154" title="New distributional records of millipedes from Bulgarian caves (Myriapoda: Diplopoda)." volume="56" year="2004">Stoev 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D13B42EB5B04A0732594D5E83763E223" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="F895E6561E4B6A8D29BB8E84306C709D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1DE9E255807442CFDA9E930567BD7FEC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="253D2C900261A33E06CBD184F8A649E5" author="Strasser, K" journalOrPublisher="Senckenbergiana Biologica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="437 - 470" refId="B53" refString="Strasser, K, 1962. Diplopoden aus Bulgarien und Jugoslawien. Senckenbergiana Biologica 43 (6): 437 - 470" title="Diplopoden aus Bulgarien und Jugoslawien." volume="43" year="1962">Strasser (1962)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on a poorly preserved female that he placed with uncertainty in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="EF9534C0F48287D54A45F561F093BA06" authorityName="Attems" authorityYear="1898" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8989B1309C04B2E8456484B29D072265" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He emphasized a very important difference in sensilla basiconica on 6th antennomere being partially exposed in 
<taxonomicName id="7044488DAFAD6BDF439BE6A404CAB893" authorityName="Strasser" authorityYear="1962" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus bulgaricus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulgaricus">
<emphasis id="17F42D864868F79726B7C2EF93E95516" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus bulgaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, while they are completely enclosed in their pit in 
<taxonomicName id="0D538FD9B159B38E01186DA128FD1CAA" authorityName="Latzel" authorityYear="1884" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Brachydesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Brachydesmus filiformis" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="filiformis">
<emphasis id="BA6ECEC889E7B50EBC20DCCDABC7C510" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Brachydesmus filiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7E0076EA8A59F6F47C04E269AF68BDAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Four years later, when males became available, 
<bibRefCitation id="311D0E50D2AA2A5EC22AC42953A8C06D" author="Strasser, K" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="325 - 385" refId="B54" refString="Strasser, K, 1966a. Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens. Annales Zoologici 23 (12): 325 - 385" title="Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens." volume="23" year="1966 a">Strasser (1966a)</bibRefCitation>
confirmed that 
<taxonomicName id="C80C3ED10588B9D9101940AE5AC20DCD" authorityName="Strasser" authorityYear="1962" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus bulgaricus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulgaricus">
<emphasis id="4716275194343F9B0096671EF87416F8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus bulgaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belonged to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="5A0E5FFFB8B18B754E02CBCCA3EA2248" authorityName="Attems" authorityYear="1898" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="91F81FB33D3D839D01B09DDC14FBBB02" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on some similarities in gonopod structures, and identified two subspecies, viz., 
<taxonomicName id="40E998004B005E47AAEB54665E00CF97" authority="bulgaricus" genus="B." lsidName="B. bulgaricus subsp. bulgaricus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subSpecies" species="bulgaricus" subSpecies="bulgaricus">
<emphasis id="F23AE3F1C8DABE2F44864FF581ADC1C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. bulgaricus bulgaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="232DC2B1811FEBA862148E0C69E26166" genus="B." lsidName="B. bulgaricus subsp. dentatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subSpecies" species="bulgaricus" subSpecies="dentatus">
<emphasis id="573C97B785497002DC2EE9DA3BB0D642" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. bulgaricus dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Subsequently, both subspecies were recognized as such by 
<bibRefCitation id="CAAC89A41AB4FED8DCE589AE6A9707F0" author="Stoev, P" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Bulgarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="145 - 154" refId="B50" refString="Stoev, P, 2004. New distributional records of millipedes from Bulgarian caves (Myriapoda: Diplopoda). Acta Zoologica Bulgarica 56 (2): 145 - 154" title="New distributional records of millipedes from Bulgarian caves (Myriapoda: Diplopoda)." volume="56" year="2004">Stoev (2004</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="111F490341D975FE026F3F0FD9047453" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-1-4020-5781-6_11" author="Stoev, P" editor="Fet, V" journalOrPublisher="Vol. 82. Biogeography and Ecology of Bulgaria. Springer, Dordrecht" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="379 - 404" refId="B51" refString="Stoev, P, 2007. Fauna and zoogeography of Myriapoda in Bulgaria. In: Fet, V, Popov, A, Eds., Monographiae Biologicae. Vol. 82. Biogeography and Ecology of Bulgaria. Springer, Dordrecht: 379 - 404, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/978-1-4020-5781-6_11" title="Fauna and zoogeography of Myriapoda in Bulgaria." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-1-4020-5781-6_11" volumeTitle="Monographiae Biologicae." year="2007">2007</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation id="2845C2BB0C99BB1F40371DFC695E1B16" author="Beron, P" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B10" refString="Beron, P, 2015. Cave Fauna of Bulgaria. East-West and National Museum of Natural History Publishers, 434 pp." title="Cave Fauna of Bulgaria. East-West and National Museum of Natural History Publishers, 434 pp." year="2015">Beron (2015)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="03D75E42F08F046A1843B78509DAFEC8" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4263.3.4" author="Bachvarova, D" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="507 - 526" refId="B9" refString="Bachvarova, D, Vagalinski, B, Doichinov, A, Stoev, P, 2017. New records of millipedes and centipedes from Bulgaria, with an annotated checklist of the Bulgarian myriapods. Zootaxa 4263 (3): 507 - 526, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4263.3.4" title="New records of millipedes and centipedes from Bulgaria, with an annotated checklist of the Bulgarian myriapods." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4263.3.4" volume="4263" year="2017">Bachvarova et al. (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. On the other hand, 
<bibRefCitation id="10D51D69D4C8654A31D5160D8A7821E1" author="Ceuca, T" journalOrPublisher="Seria Biologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B17" refString="Ceuca, T, 1992. Quelques aspects sur la faunistique, l'ecologie et la zoogeographie des diplopodes de la Region Balkanique. Bericht des naturwissenschaftlich-medizinischen Vereins in Innsbruck, Supplementum, 411-429." title="Quelques aspects sur la faunistique, l'ecologie et la zoogeographie des diplopodes de la Region Balkanique. Bericht des naturwissenschaftlich-medizinischen Vereins in Innsbruck, Supplementum, 411 - 429." year="1992">Ceuca (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="C02E581FEB112E8A917EA28D02B3095A" author="Kime, RD" journalOrPublisher="Pensoft Publishers, Sofia-Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B35" refString="Kime, RD, Enghoff, H, 2011. Atlas of European millipedes (Class Diplopoda). Vol. 1. Pensoft Publishers, Sofia-Moscow" title="Atlas of European millipedes (Class Diplopoda). Vol. 1." year="2011">Kime and Enghoff (2011)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="A0341A5242B71C53E88C2A385A490B27" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus dentatus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis id="096F4BA597D129941F772FDCB377A1DC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a separate species, 
<taxonomicName id="93122224A1CFDC4A6A0304F1EA9D8967" genus="B." lsidName="B. dentatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dentatus">
<emphasis id="64B6542E6C1224CD3BF6B541BD664DE5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. dentatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Here, we treat both taxa as separate species (see below).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6C8A2DDD5B980137CE144D36BBE82E0A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Based on the distribution of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="C3889689AA5FEDD31D59A2101A11E20E" authorityName="Antić &amp; Vagalinski &amp; Stoev &amp; Akkari" authorityYear="2022" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Balkanodesminus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Balkanodesminus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="880FF12241720CB05CD45F7A749BE2D0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Balkanodesminus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov., and the scattered distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="98C46DD0D23813F811A459DA0F3ED376" genus="B." lsidName="B. bulgaricus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="bulgaricus">
<emphasis id="4E612B5FED80AF0B82CDDA4721B295A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">B. bulgaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov., comb. nov., we are not excluding the possibility that not all records of 
<taxonomicName id="4FC4CA467E3B796B622951EA29E0171A" authorityName="Strasser" authorityYear="1962" class="Diplopoda" family="Trichopolydesmidae" genus="Bacillidesmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bacillidesmus bulgaricus" order="Polydesmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bulgaricus">
<emphasis id="F871ECBCBB12EECAA30D1FD54755D71B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bacillidesmus bulgaricus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are in fact of that species. Illustrations of gonopods are known only from the two easternmost populations, from the Mladenovata peshtera Cave (
<bibRefCitation id="446AAC8E3A0AEEC5F00B70655028F7AD" author="Strasser, K" journalOrPublisher="Annales Zoologici" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="325 - 385" refId="B54" refString="Strasser, K, 1966a. Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens. Annales Zoologici 23 (12): 325 - 385" title="Ueber Diplopoden Bulgariens." volume="23" year="1966 a">Strasser 1966a</bibRefCitation>
) and Ponora Cave (present study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
